            .cards

                .card
                    .card__number 1
                    .card__title Is all code intention-revealing?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item All code should be easy to understand for other developers
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item To make sure the code can be updated, refactored and maintained by others if needed

                .card
                    .card__number 2
                    .card__title Is all code linted/hinted?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item All code should be syntactically correct
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item To avoid unpredictable errors
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="http://jshint.com/", target="_blank") http://jshint.com
                            .list-item
                                a(href="http://eslint.org/", target="_blank") http://eslint.org/
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#js-hint", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#js-hint

                .card
                    .card__number 3
                    .card__title Is `controller as` syntax used?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Use <code>controllerAs</code>
                            .list-item Use <code>bindToController</code>
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Avoid pitfalls from scope soup
                            .list-item Target outer scopes easily from within inner scopes
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://toddmotto.com/digging-into-angulars-controller-as-syntax/", target="_blank") https://toddmotto.com/digging-into-angulars-controller-as-syntax/
                            .list-item
                                a(href="http://blog.thoughtram.io/angularjs/2015/01/02/exploring-angular-1.3-bindToController.html", target="_blank") http://blog.thoughtram.io/angularjs/2015/01/02/exploring-angular-1.3-bindToController.html

                .card
                    .card__number 4
                    .card__title Is DOM manipulation handled only by directives?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item DOM manipulation should only happen in directives
                            .list-item Use the element available in the directive compile and link function to manipulate the DOM
                            .list-item No DOM manipulation from controllers or services
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Angular is declarative with directives attached to elements. The directive then provides access via the compile or link element to this DOM element
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#directives", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#directives
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y072", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y072

                .card
                    .card__number 5
                    .card__title Are names prefixed with `$ ` avoided?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Names of variables, properties and methods should not start with <code>$</code>
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item The <code>$</code> prefix is reserved for AngularJS internals
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://google.github.io/styleguide/angularjs-google-style.html", target="_blank") https://google.github.io/styleguide/angularjs-google-style.html
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#others", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#others

                .card
                    .card__number 6
                    .card__title Is direct use of globals avoided?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Create services to wrap globals
                            .list-item Use dependency injection to inject global wrappers
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Prevents unpredictable application behavior when global is not available
                            .list-item Easier to test: allows you to mock global
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="http://jvandemo.com/how-to-properly-integrate-non-angularjs-libraries-in-your-angularjs-application/", target="_blank") http://jvandemo.com/how-to-properly-integrate-non-angularjs-libraries-in-your-angularjs-application/
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#others", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#others

                .card
                    .card__number 7
                    .card__title Are AngularJS specific directives put after standard attributes in templates?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Put AngularJS specific directives after standard attributes
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Easier to read and maintain your code
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#markup", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#markup

                .card
                    .card__number 8
                    .card__title Are built-in AngularJS dependencies injected before custom ones?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Inject built-in AngularJS dependencies before customer ones
                            .list-item Example: <code>function($rootScope, $timeout, MyDependency)</code>
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Easier to read and maintain your code
                            .list-item xxx
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#markup", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#markup

                .card
                    .card__number 9
                    .card__title Are modules named correctly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item lowerCamelCase
                            .list-item Example: myApp
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Naming convention
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y020", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y020

                .card
                    .card__number 10
                    .card__title Are controllers named correctly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item UpperCamelCase + Ctrl or UpperCamelCase + Controller
                            .list-item Example: MyCtrl or MyController
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Naming convention
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y124", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y124

                .card
                    .card__number 11
                    .card__title Are directives named correctly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item lowerCamelCase
                            .list-item Example: myDirective
                            .list-item Use <code>scope</code> instead of <code>$scope</code> in link function
                            .list-item Use custom prefix to prevent name collisions with third-party libraries
                            .list-item Don’t use <code>ng</code> prefix as it is reserved for AngularJS
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Naming convention
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y073", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y073
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y126", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y126

                .card
                    .card__number 12
                    .card__title Are filters named correctly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item lowerCamelCase
                            .list-item Example: myFilter
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Naming convention
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions

                .card
                    .card__number 13
                    .card__title Are services named correctly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item lowerCamelCase
                            .list-item Example: myService
                            .list-item UpperCamelCase if service is a Constructor
                            .list-item Example: MyContrstructorClassService
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Naming convention
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y125", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y125

                .card
                    .card__number 14
                    .card__title Are factories named correctly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item lowerCamelCase
                            .list-item Example: myFactory
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Naming convention
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#naming-conventions

                .card
                    .card__number 15
                    .card__title Are built-in AngularJS directives used whenever possible?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Use <code>ng-src</code> instead of <code>src</code>, <code>ng-href</code>instead of <code>href</code>, <code>ng-style</code>instead of <code>style</code>, etc. when dynamic values are passed
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item They make sure markup remains valid, even when expression value is not available yet
                            .list-item They are well-written and tested
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#templates", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#templates

                .card
                    .card__number 16
                    .card__title Are built-in AngularJS services used whenever possible?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Use <code>$</code> services provided by AngularJS whenever possible
                            .list-item Examples: <code>$timeout</code>, <code>$interval</code>, <code>$http</code>, …
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item These services are designed to work well with the <code>$digest</code> cycle
                            .list-item They are well-written and tested
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#angular--wrapper-services", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#angular--wrapper-services

                .card
                    .card__number 17
                    .card__title Is ng-cloak used to prevent content from flashing
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Use <code>ng-cloak</code> to initially hide elements that are only visible under certain conditions
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Prevents content flashing when page is loaded
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#templates", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#templates

                .card
                    .card__number 18
                    .card__title Is console.log() avoided?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item use <code>$log</code> service
                            .list-item use <code>$log.debug()</code> to write debug messages to the console
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item allows you to turn off debug logging in production
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$log", target="_blank") https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$log


                .card
                    .card__number 19
                    .card__title Is code minification safe?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Use array notation or $inject notation or use ng-annotate
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Code will break when minified if not written in a way that supports minification
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://docs.angularjs.org/guide/di", target="_blank") https://docs.angularjs.org/guide/di
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#manual-annotating-for-dependency-injection", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#manual-annotating-for-dependency-injection
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#minification-and-annotation", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#minification-and-annotation

    .section.section--architecture

        .section__header

            .section-title Architecture

        .section__content

            .cards


                .card
                    .card__number 1
                    .card__title Is there a component-driven structure?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Group scripts, markup and styles by feature
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Components can easily be removed
                            .list-item Locating related files is easy
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XXMvReO8-Awi1EZXAXS4PzDzdNvV6pGcuaF4Q9821Es/pub", target="_blank") https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XXMvReO8-Awi1EZXAXS4PzDzdNvV6pGcuaF4Q9821Es/pub
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#directory-structure", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#directory-structure
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y120", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y120
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y152", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y152

                .card
                    .card__number 2
                    .card__title Do directives communicate correctly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Never rely on scope inheritance e.g. <code>$scope.$parent</code>
                            .list-item Use directive controllers and <code>require</code> to let directives communicate
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item The scope hierarchy may change, breaking your code
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://docs.angularjs.org/guide/directive", target="_blank") https://docs.angularjs.org/guide/directive
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://toddmotto.com/directive-to-directive-communication-with-require/", target="_blank") https://toddmotto.com/directive-to-directive-communication-with-require/

                .card
                    .card__number 3
                    .card__title Is business logic defined in services?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Business logic should be defined in services, not in controllers
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Business logic is centralized and reusable
                            .list-item Services are really easy to test
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#services", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#services
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y035", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y035

                .card
                    .card__number 4
                    .card__title UI-Router: has a default route been configured?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Use <code>$urlRouterProvider.otherwise()</code> to specify the default route in case no route definition matches the request
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item To gracefully handle requests that do not match to a route definition
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ngRoute/provider/$routeProvider", target="_blank") https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ngRoute/provider/$routeProvider

                .card
                    .card__number 5
                    .card__title ngRoute: has a default route been configured?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Use <code>$routerProvider.otherwise()</code> to specify the default route in case no route definition matches the request
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item to gracefully handle requests that do not match to a route definition
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ngRoute/provider/$routeProvider", target="_blank") https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ngRoute/provider/$routeProvider

                .card
                    .card__number 6
                    .card__title ngRoute: are route errors handled properly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item use a <code>$routeChangeError</code> event listener to handle routing errors
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item To gracefully handle routing errors
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y112", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y112

                .card
                    .card__number 7
                    .card__title UI-Router: are state change errors handled properly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item use a <code>$stateChangeError</code> event listener to handle routing errors
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item to gracefully handle errors that occur during state transition (e.g. when a resolve fails)
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/angular-ui/ui-router/wiki#state-change-events", target="_blank") https://github.com/angular-ui/ui-router/wiki#state-change-events

                .card
                    .card__number 8
                    .card__title Are exceptions handled properly?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item decorate the <code>$exceptionHandler</code> service to handle uncaught exceptions
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item To gracefully handle uncaught exceptions
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y110", target="_blank") https://github.com/johnpapa/angular-styleguide/blob/master/a1/README.md#style-y110

                .card
                    .card__number 9
                    .card__title Are resolves used where needed?
                    .card__what
                        .list.list--what
                            .list-heading What?
                            .list-item Use the <code>resolve</code> property of a route or state to load content that is immediately required in the view
                    .card__why
                        .list.list--why
                            .list-heading Why?
                            .list-item Make sure content is loaded before view is shown
                            .list-item Prevent content flashing
                    .card__links
                        .list.list--links
                            .list-heading Links
                            .list-item
                                a(href="https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#routing", target="_blank") https://github.com/mgechev/angularjs-style-guide#routing
                            .list-item
                                a(href="http://www.jvandemo.com/how-to-resolve-angularjs-resources-with-ui-router/", target="_blank") http://www.jvandemo.com/how-to-resolve-angularjs-resources-with-ui-router/
                            .list-item
